The paper deals with combinatorial properties of graphs and their structures, which suggests that it belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper specifically focuses on permutation graphs, which are a type of intersection graphs, indicating that it could also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) category. The paper also mentions cographs and modular decomposition, which are topics related to graph theory and algorithms, suggesting that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also discusses Seidel complementation, which is a topic related to algebraic graph theory, indicating that it could belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper provides an algorithm to output forbidden Seidel minors, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category.
